column5: Went out to Wildwood conservation area near St. Marys this afternoon for a few hours and all I we could manage was one pike.  But according to a few people we talked to "you shoulda been here yesterday" Beautiful day on the water, with just a few small gusts of wind to keep the heat away.  The water was pretty murky since the algae die-off. Got this guy on a chartreuse spinnerbait and measured him out at 30"     jjcanoe
Sweet Report & nice slimy Pike!  Thanks for sharing
SLIME!!! you should have seen the net!  jjcanoe
That is a nice looking pike WTG  Rob
That's a real nice looking pike jjcanoe WTG Thanks for sharing Leechman
Haven't been to Wildwood in a few years. Always caught pike there and sometimes a nice smallie or two as well. Thanks for reminding me, maybe I'll have to make a trip out there before the snow flies.
That is a very healthy lookin' Pike!!!  Thanks for postin' that report and pic!
One is always better than nothing....nice fish!
Thanks guys, there always seem to be (at least one)willing pike in Wildwood.  jjcanoe
